		<tr>
			<td><b>Chief Merchandising Officer,&nbsp;DBL Distributing, Inc.</b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Chiarelli_Henry.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Henry Chiarelli was named President of DBL Distributing LLC, effective June 2007 following the acquisition of DBL Distributing, Inc. by Ingram Micro, a global, Fortune 100 distributor of Information Technology products and accessories. As President, Henry provides leadership and direction to the company’s marketing, merchandising, purchasing and sales functions.<br><br>
Prior to his promotion, Henry served DBL as Chief Merchandising Officer leading the teams that managed the innovative merchandising, marketing and purchasing strategies.<br><br>
Previously, Henry has served in several executive leadership roles in the consumer electronics industry. Most recently Henry had served as President of Gibson Audio (a subsidiary of Gibson Guitar). Prior to this assignment, Henry has served as President of Radioshack.com, Senior Vice President of Merchandising and Marketing for Computer City, Vice President of Merchandising for CompUSA, Vice President and General Manager of Incredible Universe and Senior Vice President of Retail Support Services for McDuff Electronics, Video Concepts and Scott Appliance. <br><br>
Henry earned his undergraduate degree in Computer Science from the Massachusetts Institute of Information Sciences and his Masters of Business Administration from Texas Christian University.<br><br> 
Henry is an active member of the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) Board of Industry Leaders and has previously served on the Board of Directors for Cobra Electronics. 
</td>
		
		
